# =============================================================================
# VietTune — Local full contributor E2E (P0 narrow: login + upload + submit)
# =============================================================================
# IMPORTANT: Playwright CHỈ load `.env` và `.env.local` — KHÔNG load file này.
# Copy các dòng E2E_* (và tuỳ chọn VITE_*) sang `.env.local` hoặc `.env`, rồi chạy test.
# Never commit `.env.local`. Playwright loads `.env` then `.env.local` (see playwright.config.ts).
# Vite dev server also reads `VITE_*` from these files when Playwright runs `npm run dev`.
# =============================================================================

# --- Playwright: contributor login (auth.setup.ts) — REQUIRED for non-skip ---
# Real contributor account that exists on YOUR backend (same API the app uses).
E2E_CONTRIBUTOR_EMAIL=contributor1@gmail.com
E2E_CONTRIBUTOR_PASSWORD=1

# --- Playwright: do NOT set this when you want the full P0 narrow upload test ---
# If set to "1", the test "P0 narrow: upload wizard → submit → item on contributions" is SKIPPED.
# E2E_SKIP_HEAVY=1

# --- Playwright: optional ---
# Leave unset for local Vite at http://localhost:3000 (default).
# PW_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000
# PW_ENV=production   # only for production-style E2E profile (different reporters / retries)

# --- Vite / app: Supabase (required in browser for upload — supabaseClient.ts throws if missing) ---
# Synced from repo `.env` (Project Settings → API in Supabase dashboard).
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://gvvmrvflustdxrhxpqso.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6Imd2dm1ydmZsdXN0ZHhyaHhwcXNvIiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJpYXQiOjE3NjgzNTg0NDgsImV4cCI6MjA4MzkzNDQ0OH0.Yoc2BCxt0OPZYYTC9oMH5vRP9GBXgNkvaE4IxNf8BSo

# Bucket used by this project (uploadService.ts default is "audio" if unset).
VITE_SUPABASE_BUCKET=VietTuneArchive

# --- Vite / app: API ---
# Default in code is "/api" (relative), which uses Vite proxy (vite.config.ts).
# For a different backend URL without changing vite.config, you can set:
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://localhost:7001/api
#
# If you use the default proxy, ensure vite.config.ts `server.proxy["/api"].target`
# points to your running local (or remote) ASP.NET API.
